ISLAMABAD, Mar 21 (APP):Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib said on Monday that the entire Pakistani nation welcomed  the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation Secretary General Hussain Ibrahim Taha.
In a tweet, the minister said that the hosting of the OIC Summit reflected Pakistan’s strong commitment to build and promote strong cooperation among the Muslim Ummah.   The minister hoped that the OIC summit will further strengthen cooperation among the Muslim world.
